Tables are used to represents the data in rows and Columns format.
We can Tables using the <table> container tag.
We can add rows to a table using <tr> Container tag. The <tr> tag nested inside the <table> tag.
we can add cells with the <td> (table data) container tag. The <td> tag nested inside the <tr> tag.
With the style attribute we can add the border to the table, rows and cells.
Tables usually includes the header.
The header is special row at the top of the table used to label each column.
using <th> tag can add the header at each cell.
To merge two or more rows, use the rowspan attribute
To merger two or more cells, use the colspan attribute.
Example:
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th><th>Age</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Amy</td><td>38</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Alex</td><td>29</td>
  </tr>
</table>

code:
<html>
    <head>
        <title>
            Tables
        </title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <table border="2" align="center">
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="Blue">Blue</td>
                <td bgcolor="Green">Green</td>
                <td bgcolor="Yellow">Yellow</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td bgcolor="Orange">Orange</td>
                <td rowspan="2" bgcolor="Brown">Black</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </body>
</html>
